<br>
And just for the record ST the Curse of cain was not the brown skin.  The curse was no priesthood.<br>
<br>
About Abel being resurrected, I have not heard or seen anything that identifies him specifically, but we do believe and this is biblical, that many of the righteous who lived before Christ were also resurrected at the time Christ was resurrected.  We also believe that other righteous individuals who lived after the time of Christ have been resurrected as well (specifically, Moroni a BoM prophet) and so it would not suprise me that Abel has been resurrected and that his descendants have recieved the priesthood through temple ordinances for the dead.<br>
<br>
You can believe anything you want to believe, but the FACT is that the vast majority of LDS are not racists.  ( I cant say all because I know a few who are)<br>
<br>
Oh and about the different quorums in the church, 30 years is not a long time considering that most of the men who serve in the First Presidency and the Quorum of the 12 Apostles  are in their 70's  80's and 90's  and have been in those quorums 20-30 years or more.  The next quorum is the 1st quorum  of the seventy and most of those guys have been there as long as I can remember and Im 36.  The men who serve in the 2nd quorum of the 70 only serve 5 years and rotate more quickly.  And you would see by a photo that it is a diverse group, Asian, Latino, European, African American, Polynesian.  These men usually serve in the area presidencies and direct the church activities in several nations under their stewardship.<br>
<br>
<br>
This is the heirarchy - Prophet &gt; First Presidency&gt; Twelve Apostles&gt; Seventy (both quorums)/Area Presidencies&gt; Stake Presidents (responsible for about 10 congregations) &gt;  Bishops (responsible for one congregation)  Again considering that most men (caucasian and all other races) do not even get called as a bishop in their life, and if they do they usually serve 5+ years as a bishop.  Before a man is called to Stake President which he usually does for 10 years,he is often a high cousellor on the stake level for a number of years.  When you take into consideration that an African American man recieved the priesthood 30 years ago, then after 1-2 years was called to serve in the Elders quorum presidencies.  did that for 2-3 years,had another calling for a few years (sunday school teacher, maybe bishops counsellor for 5 years) then Bishop for 5 years, back to the high counsel for 5 years, called as Stake President for 10 years, maybe went on a mission with his wife, (Im just throwing in all the possible scenarios), then maybe ws called as a counsellor to the mission president in the area for 3 years and then out of the 11 million members of the church 70 men are called to be in the quorums of the 70, it is not suprising that only a handful would be called to that quorum, and considering that the men usually serve over the countries that they live in, it is logical that we would have more Caucasian, Latin Asian and Polynesian men  in those quorums as the church has been established in those areas of the world for a much longer time than in Africa.   The church has only been in Russia for 13-14 years, and to my knowlege there may be only 1 or none leaders in those quorums from Russia.  We are currently talking with the Chines Govt to have the church be recognized in that country. My guess is if we were to open a mission there, the mission president and area pres would be from Hong Kong as the church has been there a long time and they speak the same language.  Although the calls are inspired, often it also has to do with logistics and the experience in the church and church leadership that those men have.  I mean they have to be the guiding force and so they have to have a deep understanding of what it means to lead a ward, a mission or a stake and that only happens with time and other leadership opportunities.<br>
<br>
The other thing is we dont think that the general authorities (those in those first 3-4 quorums) are more important to the Lord than the rest of us.  We all have a calling or responsiblity in the church.  Before Nakia was Prim. Pres I was.  Now I teach the 16 year olds.  My dad was a bishop for 5 years and then was called as scout leader.  Its not like the corporate ladder.  Not one bishop I know thought he was the right person for the job, its a lot of work and stress and nobody in their right mind would Hope for that calling.  Because on top of the calling, everyone but the first several quorums also has a 40 hour  a week job on top of caring for their flock.  <br>
<br>
The first four quorums do alot of traveling in their areas and are usually (not always) older retired gentlemen.  In the twelve apostles right now are a world renowned heart surgeon, a superior court judge, a University president all of whom gave up successful &quot;careers&quot; to serve.  Its not as if they had been campaining to get called.<br>
<br>
